des: "This side dish is the result of experimenting with some new things to jazz up my veggies. The blue cheese is definitely the star here."
ins: Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.  Place the zucchini and garlic in the skillet, cover. Cook until zucchini is just tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in tomatoes; heat until warmed through. Remove from heat; sprinkle immediately with blue cheese. Cover, and allow cheese to soften before serving.
